📌 Overview

This project analyzes employee data to uncover workforce trends, attrition patterns, and salary insights using Power BI.

🎯 Objectives

* Identify key factors driving employee attrition
* Analyze workforce distribution (department, gender, age)
* Understand salary trends across roles and education
* Enable data-driven HR decisions

📊 Key Metrics

* Total Employees: 1470
* Attrition Count: 237
* Attrition Rate: 16.12%
* Average Salary: 6.5K

📈 Dashboards Included

* Workforce Analysis
* Attrition Analysis
* Salary Insights

🔍 Key Insights

* Highest attrition in Sales and R&D
* Majority employees aged 30–39
* Low salary group shows highest attrition
* Travel frequency correlates with higher attrition

🛠 Tools Used

* Power BI
* Excel / CSV Data
* Data Cleaning & Modeling

⚡ How to Use

1. Download the .pbix file
2. Open in Power BI Desktop
3. Interact with filters and visuals

📂 Dataset

Dataset contains employee demographics, salary, job roles, and attrition status.

